OL,3,CThousands across Canary Islands to
OL,4,Cprotest tourism
OL,6,FA number of provinces have taken
OL,7,Fmatters into their own hands and are
OL,8,Fproviding guidance - and in some case
OL,9,Fstrict rules - for tourists visiting
OL,10,Fover the summer, as they try and
OL,11,Ftackle overcrowding and the problems
OL,12,Fthat come with it.
OL,14,FTourism represents nearly 12% of
OL,15,FSpain's economy but there has been
OL,16,Fgrowing pressure from locals for
OL,17,Fgovernments to put measures in place
OL,18,Fto reduce the number of visitors.
